Challenges in Implementing Controls / Reason for Customization (Business Requirement & Technical Justification):

As part of SCD compliance assessment, a review of SUID/SGID executables was performed using standard Solaris audit procedures. During the assessment, a number of Oracle Database, Oracle Grid Infrastructure and Oracle Enterprise Manager (OEM) Agent binaries were identified with SUID/SGID permissions.

Further validation was carried out using the following methods:

• Discovery of SUID/SGID binaries through system audit commands.
• Verification of system binaries using elfsign utility.
• Package ownership validation using pkgchk utility.
• Detailed file permission review using ls -l command.

The review established that the identified files belong to Oracle Database 19c, Oracle Grid Infrastructure and Oracle Enterprise Manager Agent installations. These binaries are Oracle vendor-supplied executables and are not part of the native Solaris operating system packages.

The findings were shared with the Oracle application support team for assessment. Oracle team confirmed that the identified binaries are vendor-required executables and the associated SUID/SGID permissions are necessary for normal functioning of Oracle Database, Grid Infrastructure, ASM and OEM Agent services.

Removal or modification of these permissions may result in:

• Failure of Oracle Database services.
• Failure of Oracle Grid Infrastructure and ASM operations.
• Failure of OEM Agent monitoring functions.
• Issues during database startup, maintenance and administration activities.
• Disruption of application availability and monitoring services.

Since the permissions are required by Oracle software design and operational requirements, implementation of the SCD recommendation to remove SUID/SGID permissions is not technically feasible without impacting business-critical services.

Accordingly, approval is requested to retain SUID/SGID permissions on the identified Oracle binaries and treat them as application-specific exceptions under SCD compliance requirements.

Changes Proposed under Customization:

Retain SUID/SGID permissions on the identified Oracle Database, Oracle Grid Infrastructure and Oracle Enterprise Manager Agent binaries.

